4-8-27.
Adoption of musk thistle control program.
(a) The control practices contained in the "official musk thistle control program," published by the Kansas department of agriculture on June 1, 2000, are hereby adopted by reference and shall apply to the control and eradication of musk thistle in the state of Kansas.
In addition, the biological control plans specified in K.A.R. 4-8-41 may also be used for the control and eradication of musk thistle in the state of Kansas.
(b) Copies of this publication shall be available from the Kansas[DEL: :DEL] department of agriculture, in the Topeka, Kansas office.
